<br>
Say a possible +25 to str/dex/agi over the 305 cap.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
The reason that the aforementioned OoW <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=5404&amp;source=Test" target="top">&quot;stat&quot; buffs</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> (linked to one of them), are no longer buffing stats but instead directly impacting things like &quot;increase melee damage&quot; and &quot;increase melee avoidance&quot; is because stats become progressively less and less meaningful as they raise.  Shamans pointed out that having a 100 str buff that could exceed the cap was meaningless because, per the trend of diminishing gains as stat values increased, the actual benefit would be minimal.  Apparently, SOE agreed.<br>
<br>
With that in mind, I don't see why we would be asking for stat 'over-buffing', when we could be looking for spells that directly impact these core combat values. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=983997" target="top">Fumika, Lvl 55 Disciple</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
